| name = membership number
| The membership numbers were artificially started at 501 because the DAP wanted to make itself look larger than it actually was. The membership numbers were also apparently issued alphabetically, and not chronologically, so one cannot infer that Hitler was in fact the party's 55th member. {{harvnb|Toland|1976|p=131}}. In a Hitler speech shown in ''[[Triumph of the Will]]'', Hitler makes explicit reference to his being the seventh party member and he notes the same in ''Mein Kampf''. {{harvnb|Hitler|1999|p=224}}.
