{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians --> | name = Chuck Panozzo | image = Chuck Panozzo Styx Interlochen.jpg | background = non_vocal_instrumentalist | birth_name = Charles Salvatore Panozzo | alias = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1948|9|20}} | death_date = | origin = [[Chicago, Illinois]] | instrument = Bass, vocals, guitar, piano | genre = [[Hard rock]], [[progressive rock]] | occupation = Musician, bassist | years_active = 1956–present | label = | associated_acts = [[Styx (band)|Styx]] | website = {{URL|chuckpanozzo.com/}} }}
'''Charles Salvatore "Chuck" Panozzo''' (born September 20, 1948 in [[Chicago, Illinois]]) is an American musician best known as the bass player for the rock band [[Styx (band)|Styx]]. A longtime member of Styx, he founded the group with his [[fraternal twin]] brother, drummer [[John Panozzo]], who died in July 1996, and singer/keyboardist [[Dennis DeYoung]]. He toured part-time from 1999 to 2003, and currently tours with Styx on a regular basis.
In 2001, Panozzo announced he was [[homosexuality|gay]] and living with HIV,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://classicrock.about.com/od/artistsaf/fr/panozzo_grand.htm |title = The Grand Illusion – Love, Lies, and My Life with Styx |accessdate = 2009-03-30 |author = White, Dave |publisher = [[About.com]] }}</ref> and he has been involved in campaigning for AIDS awareness and [[gay rights]]. In 2006, he spoke with ''[[Frontiers (magazine)|Frontiers]]'' for the first time about his decision to come out. The following year he released his autobiography ''The Grand Illusion: Love, Lies, and My Life With Styx.''
