'''Natalie Mayflower Sours Edwards''' (born 1978) is a senior official with the [[United States Department of the Treasury|United States Treasury]] who is employed in the [[Financial Crimes Enforcement Network|Financial Crimes division (FinCEN)]].<ref name=CBSNews2018-10-17>{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/natalie-edwards-treasury-fincen-employee-charged-with-leaking-financial-records-in-russia-probe/|title=Treasury official charged with leaking records related to Russia probe|date=October 17, 2018|work=[[CBS News]]|last=Rosenkrantz|first=Holly|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Fox2018-10-18>{{cite news|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/treasury-employee-charged-with-leaking-financial-info-of-trump-team|title=Treasury employee charged with leaking financial info on Trump team was arrested with flash drive in hand, prosecutors say|date=October 18, 2018|work=[[Fox News]]|last=Re|first=Gregg|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> She was arrested on October 16, 2018, for disclosing [[Suspicious activity report|suspicious activity reports]] (SARs) from October 2017 to October 2018 detailing [[Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections|Russia's involvement in the 2016 presidential election]] to a reporter with [[BuzzFeed News]] which published a series "The Money Trail."<ref name=CBSNews2018-10-17/><ref name=BuzzFeedMoneyTrail>{{cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/collection/themoneytrail|title=The Money Trail|date=|work=[[BuzzFeed News]]|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref> The SARs included money transfers and information about [[Maria Butina]], [[Rick Gates (political consultant)|Rick Gates]], [[Paul Manafort]], the [[Embassy of Russia in Washington, D.C.|Russian Embassy in the United States]], and a Russian firm, Prevezon Alexander, LLC., involved with [[money laundering]].<ref name=NYT2018-10-17>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/10/17/business/treasury-leak-manafort.html|title=Treasury Official Charged With Leaking Bank Reports to Journalist|date=October 17, 2018|newspaper=[[New York Times]]|last=Flitter|first=Emily|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Sputnik2018-10-17>{{cite news|url=https://sputniknews.com/world/201810171068975250-us-treasury-butina/|title=US Treasury Adviser Charged With Leaking Info on Detained Russian Citizen Butina|date=October 17, 2018|agency=[[Sputnik (news agency)|Sputnik]]|access-date=October 19, 2018}}</ref>
